[src:variational-autoencoder/unsupervised-learning] , which in this case is the step function thresholded at 2/3.
[src:variational-autoencoder/unsupervised-learning] Introduced by Radford Neal in 1992, this network applies ideas from probabilistic graphical models to neural networks.
[src:variational-autoencoder/unsupervised-learning] A key difference is that nodes in graphical models have pre-assigned meanings, whereas Belief Net neurons' features are determined after training.
[src:variational-autoencoder/unsupervised-learning] The network is a sparsely connected directed acyclic graph composed of binary stochastic neurons.
